  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">M4D Phase 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">M4D2 will target multi-ethnic displaced and migrant (guest) and host populations in the region with the aim of promoting the rights, integration and active participation of women, men and youth in the economic, social, health and cultural development of the targeted communities:             - DR Congo: Territories of Goma, Rutchuru, Niyargongo, Massisi, Bukavu, Kalehe, Uvira, Fizi
- Burundi: Provinces of Cibitoke, Bubanza, Rumonge and Bujumbura Rurale
- Rwanda: Districts of Rusizi, Rubavu, Gicumbi and Karongi</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Media for Dialogue:  Phase 2 (2019-2023) is the continuation and expansion of a regional peace- and trust-building media intervention in the Great Lakes (Rwanda, Burundi and DRC).The M4D2 project builds on the work done on the sensitisation on the main drivers of conflict deriving from the psychological and socio-political dynamics in the Great Lakes region over 2015 -2018, with a specific focus on the forced or spontaneous movement of people.  This focus on the migrant crisis is prioritized because of the challenges it poses to security and rule of law mechanisms and peaceful cohabitation in the region, namely, to good governance, cross-border trade, economic resources and socio-cultural norms as well as the potential it has for ethnic targeting, hate and dangerous speech, land-related conflicts and instability in all three countries.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 1: Reduced instrumentalization of ethnicities among national/regional host and guest populations in Rwanda, Burundi and Eastern DRC.
Objective 2: Increased media pluralism and dissemination of neutral and trustworthy information on stabilisation processes and the root causes of insecurity, identity-based manipulation and the migrant situation in all three countries and across borders. 
Objective 3: Improved cooperation between multi-ethnic, cross-border communities of Rwanda, Burundi and Eastern DRC</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This activity contributes to long term stability and peaceful coexistence within and between the three countries of the Great Lakes Region by addressing the regional drivers of conflict through a behaviour change communications intervention.</narrative>
  </description>
